SENATE BILL 266
L6, M4 6lr0816
CF HB 35
By: Senator Brooks
Introduced and read first time: January 19, 2026
Assigned to: Education, Energy, and the Environment
Committee Report: Favorable with amendments
Senate action: Adopted
Read second time: March 2, 2026
CHAPTER ______
1 AN ACT concerning
2 Local Government – Regulatory Powers – Regulation of Tree of Heaven Invasive
3 Trees
4 FOR the purpose of authorizing the governing body of a county or municipality to adopt
5 certain ordinances to regulate trees tree of heaven and certain invasive trees;
6 authorizing the governing body of a county or municipality to establish a bounty
7 program certain programs to incentivize the removal of trees tree of heaven and
8 certain invasive trees; and generally relating to local management of trees tree of
9 heaven and certain invasive trees.
10 BY repealing and reenacting, with amendments,
11 Article – Local Government
12 Section 1–1318
13 Annotated Code of Maryland
14 (2013 Volume and 2025 Supplement)
15 Preamble
16 WHEREAS, Invasive species are nonnative plants, pathogens, and animals whose
17 introduction causes harm to human health, environmental harm, or economic harm –
18 typically through unchecked growth spread; and
19 WHEREAS, The tree of heaven is a nonnative, deciduous hardwood tree that is
20 considered an invasive species throughout North America because the species spreads
EXPLANATION: CAPITALS INDICATE MATTER ADDED TO EXISTING LAW.
[Brackets] indicate matter deleted from existing law.
Underlining indicates amendments to bill.
Strike out indicates matter stricken from the bill by amendment or deleted from the law by
amendment. *sb0266*

2 SENATE BILL 266
1 quickly and aggressively, crowding out native plants with dense greenery while secreting
2 a chemical into the soil that is toxic to surrounding plants; and
3 WHEREAS, The tree of heaven is the preferred habitat for the spotted lanternfly,
4 another invasive species that is causing economic damage to the agricultural community,
5 stressing native plant populations, and generally acting as a nuisance statewide; and
6 WHEREAS, The trees on the Maryland Department of Agriculture’s Maryland
7 Invasive Plant List have been determined to be invasive, nonnative trees that cause harm
8 to human health, environmental harm, or economic harm; now, therefore,
9 SECTION 1. BE IT ENACTED BY THE GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF MARYLAND,
10 That the Laws of Maryland read as follows:
11 Article – Local Government
12 1–1318.
13 (a) (1) In this section[, “invasive] THE FOLLOWING WORDS HAVE THE
14 MEANINGS INDICATED.
15 (2) “INVASIVE bamboo” means NONNATIVE bamboo that is characterized
16 by aggressive spreading behavior, including bamboo species in the genus Phyllostachys.
17 (3) “LISTED INVASIVE TREE” MEANS ANY TREE ON THE “MARYLAND
18 INVASIVE PLANTS LIST” POSTED BY THE DEPARTMENT.
19 (4) “NATIVE TREE REPLACEMENT PROGRAM” MEANS A PROGRAM
20 WHEREBY A PERSON RECEIVES A NATIVE TREE IN EXCHANGE FOR REMOVING AND
21 ERADICATING AN INVASIVE TREE.
22 (3) (5) “TREE OF HEAVEN” MEANS THE AILANTHUS ALTISSIMA
23 TREE SPECIES.
24 (b) This section applies to all counties and municipalities.
25 (c) The governing body of a county or municipality, by ordinance, may regulate
26 invasive bamboo OR TREES OF HEAVEN, including by prohibiting a person from:
27 (1) selling invasive bamboo, LISTED INVASIVE TREES, OR TREES OF
28 HEAVEN;
29 (2) planting invasive bamboo, LISTED INVASIVE TREES, OR TREES OF
30 HEAVEN; [and]

SENATE BILL 266 3
1 (3) allowing invasive bamboo, LISTED INVASIVE TREES, to grow on the
2 property of the person without proper upkeep and appropriate containment measures,
3 including barriers or trenches; AND
4 (4) ALLOWING TREES OF HEAVEN TO GROW ON THE PERSON’S
5 PROPERTY.
6 (d) The governing body of a county or municipality may provide for the
7 enforcement of an ordinance adopted under this section by:
8 (1) requiring any damages caused by invasive bamboo OR TREES OF
9 HEAVEN OR OTHER LISTED INVASIVE TREES to be mitigated; and
10 (2) establishing a civil fine.
11 (E) THE GOVERNING BODY OF A COUNTY OR MUNICIPALITY MAY ESTABLISH
12 A BOUNTY OR NATIVE TREE REPLACEMENT PROGRAM TO INCENTIVIZE THE
13 REMOVAL AND ERADICATION OF TREES OF HEAVEN AND OTHER LISTED INVASIVE
14 TREES.
15 (F) A BOUNTY OR NATIVE TREE REPLACEMENT PROGRAM ESTABLISHED BY
16 A COUNTY OR MUNICIPALITY SHALL REQUIRE:
17 (1) AN INVASIVE TREE TO BE PROPERLY IDENTIFIED CONSISTENT
18 WITH THE SPECIES PAGE PUBLISHED BY THE UNIVERSITY OF MARYLAND
19 AGRICULTURE EXTENSION; AND
20 (2) THE INVASIVE SPECIES, AFTER BEING PROPERLY IDENTIFIED, TO
21 BE REMOVED OR ERADICATED ACCORDING TO PROFESSIONALLY ACCEPTED
22 METHODS OR CONSISTENT WITH METHODOLOGY ON THE SPECIES PAGE PUBLISHED
23 BY THE UNIVERSITY OF MARYLAND AGRICULTURE EXTENSION.
24 SECTION 2. AND BE IT FURTHER ENACTED, That this Act shall take effect
25 October 1, 2026.

